istian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peter Schenckelberg was born in 1644, in Melsbach, Neuwied, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. He married Veronica about 1675. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 12 May 1708, in his hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1644–12 Mai 1708":"1644–12. mai 1708","1661–1712":"1661–1712","1655–1684":"1655–1684","1685–1720":"1685–1720","1688–Female":"1688–Surnud","1695–1769":"1695–1769","1676–1742":"1676–1742","1681–1714":"1681–1714","1644–1708":"1644–1708","Abt 1688":"umbes 1688","1681":"1681","um 1675 1. Ehe des Mannes":"umbes 1675","März 1681":"märts 1681","1712":"1712","1644":"1644","12 Mai 1708":"12. mai 1708","1688":"1688","1655":"1655","1742":"1742","1676":"1676","1720":"1720","Abt 1695":"umbes 1695","1685":"1685","1684":"1684","1695":"1695","1661":"1661","1708":"1708","Dezember 1685":"detsember 1685","um 1685  2. Ehe des Mannes":"umbes 1685","1714":"1714","1769":"1769","um 1676":"1676","Melsbach, Altwied, Neuwied, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Melsbach, Landkreis Neuwied, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Melsbach, Neuwied, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Melsbach, Landkreis Neuwied, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Deutschland":"Saksamaa",",, Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1644–12 Mai 1708":"1644–12. toukokuuta 1708","1661–1712":"1661–1712","1655–1684":"1655–1684","1685–1720":"1685–1720","1688–Female":"1688–Kuo